title: Independent Candidate Rehan Bandookra wins PS- 110 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent Candidate, Rehan Bandookra has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-110, Karachi South-V by securing 47,450 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Sufiyan, Jamaat-e-Islami, who bagged votes 22,630.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 34.04 %.
